acquisition_process.protocol_description:
excitation channels: 561, 638 nm;
z_step: 3 µm;
detection objective: Mitutoyo BD Plan Apo 5X/0.14 (Benchtop) or Olympus MVPLAPO1x-zoom5x (mesoSPIM v.5)

Excitation channels: 561, 638 nm;
z_step: 2 µm;
Detection objective: Mitutoyo G Plan Apo 20X/0.28(t3,5);
Immersion and scanning: sample cuvette in the air (no large immersion chamber), focus interpolation mode.

experimental_variable_description:
Cell cultures were grown in M9-based media and supplemented with either:
- 0.5% v/v glycerol (Sigma-Aldrich, G9012) -  “Gly” medium; 
- 0.5% w/v glucose (D(+)-glucose anhydrous, Scientific Laboratory Supplies, CHE1806), “Glu” medium; 
- a mix of amino acids (1× MEM Non-Essential Amino Acids and 1× MEM Essential Amino Acids, both manufactured by Gibco™) added with the glucose:  “Glu-aa” medium
